latestPosts.caption:
finally.

a small letter:

this has been the biggest secret i’ve had to keep, and still of course i told the people closest to me because 365 days of doing anything leaves you a little impatient. i’d always thought ‘when i have the money, ill give this brand a makeover’, and i finally had the heart to let go of my scribbled branding and move on to who we always had the potential to be - THIS. I am ofcourse terrified of the logistical challenges as we move ahead, and my heart is in panic mode as i type this, but overall i’m eternally grateful to all the people who click ‘purchase’ everyday and help me run this crazy brand i call home. 

almost in tears, 
anshita💛

latestPosts.caption:
mission 2: decoding the curl cult 🧙‍♀️

we named it fix my curls and accidentally confused half the internet. 

so in this episode of fixing fix my curls, we’re clearing it up:
✨ it’s not just for curls
✨ it’s not about straightening
✨ it is for the beautifully in-between, the frizzy, the wavy, the “idk what this texture is but it’s doing something” gang.

and you’re invited. your hair’s invited. labels, however… are optional. 💌
